...After editing Right Click Menu

...Edit right click context menu with ease : Video Tour

...There are lots of useful applications available on the net but those applications also add their options to right click context menu. This way your right click menu looks very messy and it becomes hard to find stuff in the right click that you needed most. So we created all in one solution to this problem a tool called Right Click Editor in Right Click Enhancer Professional's arsenal.
...Right Click Editor is a right click context menu editor tool that can help you remove or disable unwanted entries from your right click context menu. &lt;a href=&quot;
http://rbsoft.org/images/Copy_files_with_send_to_menu_shortcuts.png&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://rbsoft.org/images/Copy_files_with_send_to_menu_shortcuts.png&lt;/a&gt;

...Copy files and folders with ease

...Windows has very useful feature Send to menu but it only useful when we want to copy things to flash drive otherwise its useless. Now take the advantage of this very useful feature with help of Send To Manager.
Send To Manager allows you to add new folder shortcut to your send to menu. After adding the shortcut to send to menu you can send file to that folder directly.
...You can also speedup your copying or moving process with Right Click Tweaker's Copy to folder and Move to folder. These options when clicked presents with all the folders inyour right click menu just selcet the folder where you whant to paste and click Copy or Move and you're done. So you don't need to go to the folder to paste your files or folders.
 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://rbsoft.org/images/Create_new_files_with_new_menu.png&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://rbsoft.org/images/Create_new_files_with_new_menu.png&lt;/a&gt;
...Edit right click new menu with ease

...Some times users of the PC do some repetitive tasks while creating their documents. These repetitive steps are usually avoided with help of templates.You can avoid repetitive formatting while creating your documents using windows feature called new menu inside right click menu but windows doesn't have any tool that allows you to edit new menu. Now take control of your new menu with New Menu Editor tool.
...New Menu Editor allows you to add new file type to your new menu so you can create new files of that type with one click.
...You also have the option to remove existing entries from your new menu. You can add two types of entries in your new menu. You can add 0 byte file with no data in it which is best suited for text files or you can add template file. When user choose this template type of entry to create new file, all the data in the template will preserved on new file creation. This proves very useful for HTML templates and other formatted documents like Word, Power Point  and Excel documents.
...Edit your file associations with ease

...Some times file association of some file behave abnormally. This issue can be fixed using File Types Editor.
...File Types Editor allows you associate File Type with extension. For example if you want to use Windows Media Player for MP3 files and your current association for MP3 file is for VLC Media Player then you can do the file association using File Types Editor.
...It also lets you modify right click entries for context menu of different file types.
...Export anything to registry file

...You can export all the changes from any of the tools to registry file. This way ...you can apply those changes instantly on other PC by double clicking the registry file.
